f=Executive Office/echo/marketplace/investor-update-generator/references/what_makes_good_updates.md · h1:What Makes Good Investor Updates=Investors read dozens monthly updates month. ones produce help, raise reputation, keep cap table aligned share patterns; ones don't share different set. · h3:All-positive momentum=Updates never lowlight tell investors either (a) you're paying attention risks, (b) you're managing them away update. bad. · h3:Vague metrics="Strong growth" without number, "promising pipeline" without dollars. Investors discount what they can't quantify. · h3:Generic asks="Let know you help" produces help. Specificity unlocks value. · h3:Inconsistent reporting=Defining MRR one way March another way April erodes trust. Pick definitions; stick them. · h3:Long format=2000+ word updates skim-rate-dropping. investors 5-10 minutes read; format budget. · h3:No cadence=Quarterly updates Series company sparse. Skipping months without explanation produces silence anxiety. · h2:Distribution=**Investors only:** safer sensitive data; minimum surface area. **Investors advisors:** often appropriate; advisors act asks. **Extended network (helpful operators):** broader help potential; risk leakage. Pick list size you sustain. names plenty Series · h2:Sensitive Information=founders share more, less: · h2:Sensitive Information=**Always share:** topline metrics, runway, key risks, asks, **Often share:** detailed pipeline, competitive moves, churn analysis, **Sometimes share:** exact ARR (some prefer growth instead), specific customer names, **Rarely share:** salary specifics, legal-sensitive context, trade secrets · h2:Sensitive Information=bar: you comfortable leaked? not, leave out share verbally. · h2:Common Mistakes=**Skipping months.** Once cadence breaks, it's hard restart. **Update PR.** Updates aren't pitches. audience already in. **Burying lede.** Whatever's important say first. **No metrics writing.** Verbal updates don't substitute written. **Wall text.** Use sections, bullets, bold scan-ability. **Different definitions monthly.** "MRR includes excludes annual contracts" needs stay constant. **Asks end.** Asks early enough they survive skim-reads.